The public has very little regard for an entity that embodies brutality and corruption.Yet, amid all the vile attributes associated with the police, still, it is a necessary evil. Recently, a senior police officer directed the public to change its negative attitudes towards law enforcers. Such attitudes are hurting the standing of the police, the honcho reckoned.
True. Attitudes are powerful. They direct behaviour. Attitudes determine success or failure of enterprises. That is why when a significant stakeholder develops a negative attitude towards your enterprise, you are alarmed.



