Indeed, if the Police Service were a commercial enterprise, it would have closed shop eons ago. This is because the public has very little regard for an entity that embodies brutality and corruption.
Yet, amid all the vile attributes associated with the police, still, it is a necessary evil. The police system is a critical cog in the architecture of justice, more so in liberal democracies like Kenya.



