Reconstructing the public image of the police will take time and will be discomfiting to a sect that benefits from the current paralysis.
The blotted image of the police is systemic and historical. To change the negative attitudes, the police must also change. It means the public must experience a fresh congenial, but firm Police Service. An unimpeachable system truly living to its mantra of ‘Utumishi kwa Wote’. 
